"n./adj. 代用品(的)；权宜之计(的) 【英】 n./ adj. 权宜之计(的)，代用 品(a substitute; temporary expedient) 【记】 组合词：make(作)+sh ift(转移，改变) 【例】 Buttons were the child's makeshifts for toys. n. /adj. 权宜之计(临时替代其它事物的东西) 【记】make作出, shift转移: 对一件事情作出转移－权宜之计 【记】make + shift 换班，转移 makeshift  also make-shift, 1560s, as a noun, ""shifty person, rogue,"" from make (v.) + shift (v.). Adjectival sense of ""substitute"" is first recorded 1680s. Compare make-sport ""a laughing stock"" (1610s)."
